==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-rag.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}} 
# A piece of cloth torn off; a tattered piece of cloth; a shred; a tatter; a fragment.
# Hence, mean or tattered attire; worn-out dress.
# A shabby, beggarly fellow; a ragamuffin.
# A coarse kind of rock, somewhat cellular in texture.
# A ragged edge.
# A sail, or any piece of canvas.
# A piece of [[ragtime]] music.
#:''The song mapleleaf '''rag''' has a pleasant, bouncy tune.''

====Quotations====
'''a coarse kind of rock'''
*'''2003''': the three walls around the garden, each one of thirty-three feet, were built out of three layers of stome &mdash; pebble stone, flint and '''rag''' stone. &mdash; Peter Ackroyd, ''The Clerkenwell Tales,'' 2003, page 1.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|rag||g}}
# To [[scold]] or [[rail]] at; to rate; to [[tease]]; to torment; to banter.

